Text.Value: Death-curse be damned, we're heading to Moonrise.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Addressed to the room in general
EditorData.NodeContext: Addressed to the room in general
EditorData.logicalname: at least one other loyalist still alive

Text.Value: I... I was wrong. I must free them.
*The mark glows, but you feel nothing in response. Your illithid power is beyond reach until you rest.*
The gnomes won't survive the curse. What good is a gift of corpses?
FREE THEM, OR ELSE.
Damn slaves better survive the journey before the death-curse chokes 'em.
The gnomes should be able to go where they please. They are not the duergar's to keep.
Read Thrinn's thoughts.
Speak up, chief. You can't just let the clan keep them.
*Your mind lurches, reeling suddenly as if... bitten.*
Leave.
*Something stirs deep within you, hungry and alert... it's taking something you'll never get back.*
Call on the parasite, connect with Thrinn. 'The gnomes must go free.'
Fine. I'm in no mood to butt heads with another True Soul.
You sicken me. It's time I cut you down once and for all.
Brittle are the foundations upon which the houses of tyrants are built. It seems I judged you to be less brittle than you really are.
But the Absolute's blessed me. She'll guide my steps.
What can you tell me about the General?
Nothing but cursed shadows from here to Moonrise.
You got it, jargh. In the Absolute's name!
C'mon, then. Try me.
Draw on the power within to enforce your will.
*The presence deep in your mind is awake, unblinking. This is it. A single word pervades your consciousness: 'Soon'.*
I am freeing these gnomes. Just try and stop me.
I'll tell him how Nere failed, how the Absolute favoured me. He'll promote me to True Soul - I feel it in my bones.
I'm going to Moonrise. And that death-curse won't be stopping me.
You mentioned a death-curse. Is the journey so dangerous?
The Absolute will clear my way. Not one shred of doubt.
I'm... speechless. Wow. Just... just wow.

EditorData.NodeContext: Appalled at what the player has just done.

Text.Value: Get out of here, squat-pricks - before I toss you all in the fires.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Addressed to the room in general
EditorData.NodeContext: Addressed to the room in general

Text.Value: Shit - you're on to something, hate to say.
*Your mind is full, bursting with ecstasy and terror. Finally, it is coming. You are becoming.*
What about the slaves? What happens to them?

EditorData.logicalname: At least one gnome still alive

Text.Value: Draw on the power within to enforce your will.
My arse, She did. If the Absolute wants 'em gone, the General himself will tell me.
Yes. They will serve the Absolute's Chosen.
Call on the parasite, connect with Thrinn. 'The gnomes must go free.'
What else? They're coming with us. A gift to the General from his new faithful.
*A strange symbol glows, marked on their flesh, and something within you stirs in response.*

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: Delete if you are talking to a companion.

Text.Value: I'll be damned. Nere's gone and kicked it.
*As the symbol glows, power courses through you. Authority.*
I know what you're trying. And I won't stand for it, jargh!
It's time I met the General in the flesh.
*A shadow swims across your vision, and a familiar voice tells you to be calm. You are loved.*
*A shiver runs across your mind... You feel sated.*
*You focus on the source of the power, but it is quiet and still. It needs to rest.*
Attack Thrinn.
Hah. Bastard can dream on. Right?
*Your blood runs quicker, feeding the gnawing absence at the centre of your mind.*
Don't you get it? Nere fell - and I'm the one standing.
Your heart made of stone? They deserved freedom - and you denied it.
Listen, you pricks. Grab your gear and get ready to move.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Addressed to the room in general
EditorData.NodeContext: Addressed to the room in general
EditorData.logicalname: at least one other loyalist still alive

Text.Value: Try it, jargh. Let's find out who the Absolute favours.
Absolute's Chosen, Nere said. Building an army at Moonrise - nothing goes without his say-so.
Did She now? Well - not the time to go debatin' with a True Soul.
Good idea. They will make a fine offering.
The surface is dangerous. Are you sure it's safe to travel?

EditorData.logicalname: Player got surface warning at elevator

Text.Value: Then show me. And may the Absolute bless the victor!

Synopsis: The player sided with Nere, but Nere died in combat. Thrinn announces her plan: to travel to Moonrise.
